# Every file requires an approving review from the listed owner(s) before
# a PR targeting a protected branch (currently `main`) can be merged.
# Combined with "Require review from Code Owners" in branch protection,
# this is what guarantees your personal sign-off on every change --
# including PRs opened from forks by external contributors.
#
# Format: <path-pattern> <owner1> [<owner2> ...]
# Last matching pattern wins.
#
# Update the owner below if your personal GitHub handle differs from the
# repo owner. Add per-path overrides as the project grows, e.g.:
#   terraform/  @430am @some-teammate
#   docs/       @430am
* @430am
